http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Public-sector-banks-responsible-for-country%E2%80%99s-growth-in-all-sectors-says-Prabhat-Patnaik/article14017658.ece

Stating that the Indian economy has cut out different tasks for private and public sector banks, eminent economist Prabhat Patnaik on Sunday said that if PSU banks start functioning like private banks, the social responsibilities of the banking sector gets lost.Delivering the keynote address at the 20th All India Conference of Corporation Bank Officers’ Organisation here, Mr. Patnaik, who was also the vice-chairman of the Kerala State Planning Board, said that world over, nationalised banks have been performing well. The government first should stop pressuring public sector banks to lend to corporates, he added.Mr. Patnaik said without public sector banks, India could not have achieved the Green Revolution and strengthening the priority sector, including agriculture, fishery, small businesses and other areas. As the credit regulation is in the hands of PSU banks, the benefits have reached the last man in the country, he said.He noted that the economic slowdown across the world had shrunken the market, including affecting exports from India. As such, PSU banks had to look at other avenues, including strengthening the domestic market.The domestic market can be strengthened through promoting education, health and agriculture in the rural sector, Mr. Patnaik noted.No to privatisationAll India Bank Officers’ Confederation President Y. Sudarshan said various trade unions in the banking sector were completely opposed to attempts by the Union government to privatise PSU banks.Mr. Sudarshan also said the unions were opposed to the proposed Industrial Relations Bill, seeking to consolidate various laws pertaining to trade unions and other industry-related activities.The two-day conference is being attended by over 2,500 delegates from across the country and will deliberate on issues concerning public sector banks.